    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If you submit the transaction via your miner node, it will track it as \"local\" and allow mining without fees. This is mostly meant to allow mining pools to do their own payouts without gas. If you were to have a 2 node network and send the transaction from the non-miner, it wouldn't mine it any more.",
